pig bucket
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:formerly, receptacle for kitchen waste to be fed to pigs; a (domestic) slop-tin for organic or food wastes, originally to be fed to pigs.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:pig tub, pig barrel
Pronunciation:
Notes: aka pig-bucket, pigs' bucket, pig's bucket
